        </p>
        <p>
            Using the site implies full acceptance of these terms. If you do not agree with
            them, please do not use the service.
        </p>
    </section>

    <hr class="hx-rule">

    <section id="access">
        <h2>2. Access to the service</h2>
        <p>
            Browsing the encyclopedia is free and requires no account. An account is only
            needed for personal features: builds, favorites and profile.
        </p>
        <p>
            The publisher strives to keep the service available at all times but does not
            guarantee uninterrupted availability (see <a href="#liability">section 8</a>).
        </p>
    </section>

    <hr class="hx-rule">

    <section id="account">
        <h2>3. User account</h2>
        <p>By creating an account, you agree to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>provide <strong>accurate</strong> information and keep it up to date (in particular your email address);</li>
            <li>create only <strong>one account per person</strong>;</li>
            <li>choose a strong password and keep it <strong>confidential</strong> — actions performed from your account are deemed to be yours;</li>
            <li>notify the publisher without delay of any unauthorized use of your account.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Your profile is <strong>private by default</strong>; you can make it public from its
            settings. The processing of your data is described in the
            <a href="{{ path('app_legal_privacy') }}">privacy policy</a>.
        </p>
    </section>

    <hr class="hx-rule">

